  "body": "I use standalone node and ethers.js lib. My config looks like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.5.16\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      mining: {\r\n        auto: false,\r\n        interval: [2000, 3000],\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nI subsribed to new block events:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst provider = new ethers.providers.WebSocketProvider(\"ws://localhost:8545\");\r\n\r\nprovider.on(\"block\", (blockNumber) => {\r\n  console.log(new Date(), blockNumber);\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt works fine until I begin to send transaction to this local node. Then my event handler starts to receive duplicated new block events.\r\n\r\n```\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:27.293Z 13195178\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:27.964Z 13195179\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:28.759Z 13195180\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:29.367Z 13195181\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:30.367Z 13195182\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:30.639Z 13195183\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:31.045Z 13195183\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:31.056Z 13195183\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:31.386Z 13195183\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:31.404Z 13195184\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:31.407Z 13195184\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:31.413Z 13195184\r\n2021-12-04T19:05:32.345Z 13195184\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I stop send transactions, duplicated blocks events disappears, and subscription works as expected - single event for each block.",
