    "body": "This is even simpler to reproduce (and a worse problem):\r\n\r\n1. Start a node with automining disabled (no interval mining)\r\n2. Start the script that @molfar shared that subscribes to new block events via ws\r\n3. Send a plain tx: `  await network.provider.send(\"eth_sendTransaction\", [{ from: \"0xf39fd6e51aad88f6f4ce6ab8827279cfffb92266\", to: \"0xf39fd6e51aad88f6f4ce6ab8827279cfffb92266\" }]);`\r\n\r\nThe script will log `1` three times. And if you send that tx again, the script will log `1` three times again (instead of `2`)!",
